Name: Gamma Weed
Description:
A luminous, leafy flowering plant that thrives in radioactive biomes and can be cultivated to yield a bountiful harvest.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Ensure Radioactive climate before planting outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>4 hours<>
Additional: 50 Gamma Root in roughly 4 hours of real time

Name: Fungal Cluster
Description:
A spherical fungus with internal gills, found only in toxic biomes. Fungal Clusters can be transplanted for cultivation, yielding a bountiful harvest.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Ensure Toxic climate before planting outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>4 hours<>
Additional: 50 Fungal Mould in roughly 4 hours of real time

Name: Frostwort
Description:
A large crystal flower with radiant blue blooms, found only in snowy biomes. Frostwort can be farmed and makes a reliable crop, and its adaptation to harsh conditions results in highly frequent harvests.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Ensure Frozen climate before planting outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>1 hour<>
Additional: 50 Frost Crystal in roughly 1 hour of real time

Name: Venom Urchin
Description:
A small, innocuous looking plant whose leaves periodically secrete a small amount of potent Sac Venom, a valuable trading commodity.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Cannot be planted outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>3 hours 20 mins<>
Additional: 1 Sac Venom in roughly 3 hours 20 minutes of real time

Name: Solar Vine
Description:
This 'living rock' is adapted to live in the extreme heat of scorched biomes. However, it can be farmed in most environments and, once established, yields a moderate harvest.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Ensure Hot climate before planting outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>16 hours<>
Additional: 50 Solanium in roughly 16 hours of real time

Name: Gutrot Flower
Description:
A foul-smelling, farmable flower that replicates the chemical structure of faecal matter. When planted inside, yields a harvest of Faecium.

A good alternative to collecting Faecium by hand, which requires <TECHNOLOGY>feeding creatures<> and then <TECHNOLOGY>harvesting their droppings<>. Gutrot Flowers must be grown in a <TECHNOLOGY>Hydroponics Tray<>.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>4 hours<>
Additional: 25 Faecium in roughly 4 hours of real time

Name: Gravitino Host
Description:
A strange, potentially parasitic plant that yields an occasional harvest of the highly tradable commodity, Gravitino Balls.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Cannot be planted outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>2 hours<>
Additional: 1 Gravitino Ball in roughly 2 hours of real time

Name: Mordite Root
Description:
An inedible tuber that produces a small yield of Mordite crystals.

A peaceful alternative to the process of harvesting Mordite from the <TECHNOLOGY>corpses of creatures<>. Mordite Root must be grown in a <TECHNOLOGY>Hydroponics Tray<>.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>8 hours<>
Additional: 25 Mordite in roughly 8 hours of real time

Name: Echinocactus
Description:
Native to barren biomes and capable of withstanding long periods of drought, Echinocactus is an edible succulent that responds well to cultivation, yielding a large but occasional harvest.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Ensure Barren climate before planting outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>16 hours<>
Additional: 100 Cactus Flesh in roughly 16 hours of real-world time

Name: Star Bramble
Description:
A medium-sized, farmable plant that yields an occasional harvest of valuable Star Bulbs.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Ensure Lush climate before planting outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>4 hours<>
Additional: 25 Star Bulbs in roughly 4 hours of real time

Name: Albumen Pearl Orb
Description:
A medium-sized, farmable Crystal Orb that yields an occasional harvest of valuable Albumen Pearls.

Suitable for hydroponic indoor planting. Cannot be planted outdoors.

Approximate growing time: <TECHNOLOGY>80 mins<>
Additional: 1 Albumen Pearl in roughly 2 hours of real time

Name: NipNip
Description:
This medicinal herb is known for its pungent buds, which are harvested to produce Gek Nip. NipNip thrives in dank environments, and often grows as a weed.

Suitable for hydroponic planting indoors. Needs a tropical or humid climate before planting outdoors.
Additional: 1 NipNip Buds in roughly 4 hours of real time

Description:
A large decorative fruit tree.

Fruit form, toxicity and existence will vary according to local climatic and pollinator conditions.

Name: Spindle Tree
Description:
A thin, non-fruiting tree. Root system is integrated with highly-adapted fungal symbiotes.

Supplied with its own mushrooms for ease of establishment. Fungus is non-toxic and non-spreading.

Name: Evergreen Tree
Description:
A hardy evergreen tree, able to survive in a wide-range of climates.

Waxy leaves with a silvery underside provide excellent light harvesting abilities, as well as year-round interest and colour.

Name: Carnivorous Bush
Description:
A medium-sized decorative plant. Each of its leaves is covered in a thin film of sticky latex. Insects that land on these leaves are slowly absorbed by digestive hormones mixed in with the glue.

Avoid accidental skin contact.

Name: Dwarf Palm
Description:
A squat, easily-managed form of the larger palm species.

Place outdoors to attract wildlife and to purify the air.

Name: Curious Corn
Description:
Sprouting decorative corn. Comes in a variety of colours. May attract decorative wildlife.

Unable to reproduce naturally. Must be hand-pollinated.

Name: Small Aquarium
Description:
A small observatory unit for studying aquatic behaviours.

Completely self-contained, with its own renewable energy source, pump array, and self-cleaning filtration systems.

Name: Curly Coral
Description: A delicate marine invertebrate, cultivated for potted growth. Its distinctive looping structure gives it an attractive whimsical appearance.

Name: Aquatic Crystal
Description: An eye-catching cluster of crystallised oceanic minerals. These crystals grow in a shard-like structure, and feature an unusual marbled colouration.

Name: Candelabra Bloom
Description: A striking plant featuring luminescent, orb-shaped flowers. This domestic variety has adapted to absorb and process oxygen from any source, whether growing on land or underwater.

Name: Barnacle
Description:
A tenacious arthropod, naturally found encrusting stationary or slow-moving underwater objects.

This variety can be encouraged to affix itself to a chosen position, adding an aged marine appearance to bases.

Name: Blue Firework
Description: A luxury firework, rich in magnesium and indium. Ignite to create glittering displays in the sky. Place launch tube via the Build Menu<> (BUILD_MENU<>). Warning<>: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

Name: Pocket Reality Generator
Description:
An exclusive decorative curiosity for bases.

A model of reality itself, as viewed from the perspective of an impossible observer. Infinite levels of detail wait to be discovered by the viewer with a powerful enough lens.

Name: Terrarium
Description:
A small observatory unit for studying animal behaviours.

Completely self-contained, complete with inbuilt nutrient processor, air purifier and faecal disposal system.

Name: Sail Palm
Description:
A large-leafed, heat resistant tree.

Its broad fronds are laced with minerals, forming a protective barrier against the harsh sunlight of its native conditions.

Name: Globe Tree
Description:
A thin tree with a large, fleshy root system, well adapted to hot climates.

Root bulb may be tapped for a source of drinkable liquid, but this is not advised outside of the most dire circumstances.

Name: Rock Garden
Description: A garden module, complete with decorative mineral formation and built-in capillary matting for optimum humidity control.

Name: Small Wooden Door
Description: A small door to insert in a wooden doorframe

Name: Wooden Power Door
Description:
A <TECHNOLOGY>power-operated door<>. Can be connected to a <STELLAR>power grid<> and operated using various switches.

Fashioned from <TITLE>pressure-treated, resin-injected wood<>.

Name: Wooden Inner Roof Corner
Description:
A vital structure roof piece, critical when building angular roofs.

Fashioned from <TITLE>pressure-treated, resin-injected wood<>.

Name: Small Metal Door
Description: A small door to insert in a metal doorframe

Name: Metal Power Door
Description:
A <TECHNOLOGY>power-operated door<>. Can be connected to a <STELLAR>power grid<> and operated using various switches.

Fashioned from <TITLE>high-strength metal alloys<>.

Name: Red Firework
Description: A luxury firework, rich in magnesium and cadmium. Ignite to create glittering displays in the sky. Place launch tube via the Build Menu<> (BUILD_MENU<>). Warning<>: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

Name: Metal Inner Roof Corner
Description:
A vital structure roof piece, critical when building angular roofs.

Fashioned from <TITLE>high-strength metal alloys<>.

Description: A small door to insert in a concrete doorframe

Name: Concrete Power Door

A <TECHNOLOGY>power-operated door<>. Can be connected to a <STELLAR>power grid<> and operated using various switches.

Fashioned from <TITLE>reinforced concrete slabs<>.

Description:
A vital structure roof piece, critical when building angular roofs.

Fashioned from <TITLE>reinforced concrete slabs<>.

Name: Lantern
Description: A low-energy consumption light, with an extended lifespan and fully recyclable components.

Name: Anomaly Decal
Description:
An exclusive placeable decal, to add flair and decoration to bases.
This decal depicts a Traveller Anomaly.

Name: Wooden Triangle
Description: A basic flooring piece of wooden construction, this simple shape allows the creation of a huge array of diverse structures.

Name: Small Wooden Triangle
Description: A basic flooring piece of wooden construction, this simple shape allows the creation of a huge array of diverse structures.

Name: Metal Triangle
Description: A basic flooring piece of metal construction, this simple shape allows the creation of a huge array of diverse structures.

Description: A basic flooring piece of metal construction, this simple shape allows the creation of a huge array of diverse structures.

Name: Concrete Triangle
Description: A basic flooring piece of concrete construction, this simple shape allows the creation of a huge array of diverse structures.

Description: A basic flooring piece of concrete construction, this simple shape allows the creation of a huge array of diverse structures.

Name: Blue Light
Description: A coloured light for illuminating and decorating bases.

Name: Pink Light
Description: A coloured light for illuminating and decorating bases.

Name: Yellow Light
Description: A coloured light for illuminating and decorating bases.

Name: Green Light
Description: A coloured light for illuminating and decorating bases.

Name: Light Floor
Description:
A special construction module fashioned entirely from light-emitting panels. Can be used to construct floors of light.

This floor panel may be recoloured before or after placement. Requires <STELLAR>power<> to operate.

Name: ByteBeat Device
Description:
An advanced audio generator, allowing the user to <TECHNOLOGY>synthesise complex musical arrangements<>.

Multiple devices may be placed in sequence or connected to <STELLAR>lights<> to generate spectacular displays.

Name: ByteBeat Cable
Description:
Advanced cabling, designed to link one or more <TECHNOLOGY>Bytebeat Generators<> or to connect a <TECHNOLOGY>Bytebeat Switch<> to the network.

The signal will synchronize connected lights and device to the generated waveform.

Name: Bytebeat Switch
Description: A musical switching device, designed to interpret waveform signals generated by a <TECHNOLOGY>Bytebeat Generator<> and output electrical impulses to connected <TECHNOLOGY>lights<> and other devices.

Name: Exosuit Backpack
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

A tough, modular backpack unit. Its styling calls to mind a previous era of exploration.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Rainbow Jetpack Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Precisely calibrated multi-chromatic injectors alter the Jetpack's output, turning the exhaust trail into a vibrant display of colour.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Antimatter Jetpack Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Baryon suppressors alter the Jetpack's output, giving a distinct black tint to its signature trail.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Red Jetpack Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Cadmium injection nozzles add a bold red flair to the Jetpack's output.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Green Jetpack Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Emeril injection nozzles add a rich green flair to the Jetpack's output.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Blue Jetpack Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Indium injection nozzles add a dazzling blue flair to the Jetpack's output.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Chromatic Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

Precisely calibrated multi-chromatic injectors alter the Pulse Engine's output, turning the exhaust trail into a vibrant display of colour.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Stealth Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

Baryon suppressors alter the Pulse Engine's output, giving a distinct black tint to its signature trail.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Cadmium Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

Cadmium injection nozzles add a bold red flair to the Pulse Engine's output.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Emeril Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

Emeril injection nozzles add a rich green flair to the Pulse Engine's output.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Golden Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

Gold injection nozzles add a dazzling gold flair to the Pulse Engine's output.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Writhing Bush
Description:
A native of radioactive worlds, this curiously meaty succulent seems to sway gently even when the air is still...

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Umbrella Tree
Description:
This decorative tree has evolved to cope with high levels of background radiation. Its central glowing core attracts wildlife and is in no way a sense organ. It does not watch you.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Entwining Tree
Description:
This beautiful statement tree thrives in the heat of intense gamma radiation. To ensure survival in non-native environments, a chunk of high-energy material has been embedded in the trunk.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Blistering Mushroom
Description:
This swollen protuberance grows rapidly from a fine network of underground spores. Greatly improves nearby soil quality.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Watchful Protrusion
Description:
While this plant can be cultivated as a crop, consumption is not advised.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Tentacle Spire
Description:
This delightful architectural floral combines two highly popular aesthetics: wriggling tentacles and giant fungi.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Bewitching Cactus
Description:
Elegant feathery filaments run around this desert plant, increasing the surface area for moisture absorption. They also look very fetching.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Celebratory Cactus
Description:
Delightful succulent baubles, these lovely plants top their bulbous bodies with a show of beautiful flowers.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Succulent Tree
Description:
The bark on this tree is misleading. Neither rough nor hard, its flesh is instead soft and moist to the touch. Wrinkles in the surface store extra water for times of hardship.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Hardy Shrub
Description:
This tough conifer pumps its sap with anti-freezing enzymes, allowing it to survive unimaginably low temperatures.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Frozen Planter
Description:
A snow-filled stone trough. This is the perfect home for the small, tough plants that grow on ice-bound worlds.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Ancient Conifer
Description:
This tree lives on an almost geological time scale. Low heat and light levels in their native habitat restrict growth to mere millimeters each season. A sample this size is a botanical marvel.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Marine Rock
Description:
A pleasing mineral formation, crystalised from oceanic salts. May also contain aquatic fossils and/or lifeforms.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Mineral Arch
Description:
A remarkable piece of geological geometry. A stable load-bearing arch, infused with curiously angular solid geodes.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Gem-Encrusted Rock
Description:
Once a discarded byproduct of deep-level crystal mining, the aesthetic value of the rocks is now better appreciated.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Curious Fauna Banner
Description:
Demonstrate your interest in strange and unusual animal life with this exclusive <STELLAR>Personal Flair<>.

Apply this banner to your profile at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Banner Of The Blob
Description:
Show off your love of gentle blob-like creatures and their delicious honey with this exclusive <STELLAR>Personal Flair<>.

Apply this banner to your profile at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Specialist Polo Banner
Description:
Specialist Polo hopes you enjoy this exclusive <STELLAR>Personal Flair<>. May it bring you joy on your travels!

Apply this banner to your profile at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Priest Entity Nada Banner
Description:
Bring Priest-Entity Nada into your personal convergence by equipping this exclusive <STELLAR>Personal Flair<>.

Apply this banner to your profile at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Galactic Hub Banner
Description:
Equip this exclusive <STELLAR>Personal Flair<> and explore together!

Apply this banner to your profile at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Fine And Tasty Banner
Description:
Demonstrate your commitment to delicious pan-galactic cookery with this exclusive <STELLAR>Personal Flair<>.

Apply this banner to your profile at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Orbital Exocraft Materialiser
Description:
Construction allows the user to summon any owned Exocraft while in the same system as their freighter.

Interfaces with the <STELLAR>Exosuit Quick Command Menu<> to ease of use.

Name: Electrical Cloaking Unit
Description:
Device to enable a wireless aesthetic in habitable bases.

Constructing the <TECHNOLOGY>Electrical Cloaking Unit<> within a powered base will reduce the visual prominence of all local <TECHNOLOGY>Electrical Wiring<>. Hidden wires will continue to supply electricity, provided they are sufficiently powered.

Name: Emergency Heater
Description: A localised heating unit, recovered from the wreckage of a derelict freighter.

Name: Emergency Light
Description: An emergency floor light, recovered from the wreckage of a derelict freighter.

Name: Floral Canister
Description: A containment vessel for alien flora, recovered from the wreckage of a derelict freighter.

Name: Crew Locker
Description: A sturdy personal locker, recovered from the wreckage of a derelict freighter.

Name: Heavy-Duty Furniture
Description: Robustly constructed interior decoration, created with the needs of industrial spacefaring in mind.

Name: Salvage Crate
Description: A versatile storage unit, recovered from the wreckage of a derelict freighter.

Name: Storage Unit
Description: A versatile storage unit, recovered from the wreckage of a derelict freighter.

Name: Large Storage Unit
Description: A versatile storage unit, recovered from the wreckage of a derelict freighter.

Name: Secure Briefcase
Description: A versatile storage unit, recovered from the wreckage of a derelict freighter.

Name: Crew Footlocker
Description: A sturdy personal locker, recovered from the wreckage of a derelict freighter.

Name: Industrial Bench
Description: Robustly constructed interior decoration, created with the needs of industrial spacefaring in mind.

Name: Industrial Pallet
Description: Robustly constructed interior decoration, created with the needs of industrial spacefaring in mind.

Name: Industrial Barrel
Description: A versatile storage unit, recovered from the wreckage of a derelict freighter.

Name: Sample Containment
Description:
A sinister experimental tube, recovered from the wreckage of a derelict freighter.

Internal lifesigns: <FUEL>INDISTINCT<>

Name: Hazard Decal
Description:
An exclusive placeable decal, to add a touch of macabre decoration to bases.

This decal serves as a warning to all those who would venture past it.

Name: Warning Decal
Description:
An exclusive placeable decal, to add a touch of macabre decoration to bases.

This decal depicts the final state of an unfortunate soul.

Name: Horrific Decal
Description:
An exclusive placeable decal, to add a touch of macabre decoration to bases.

This decal depicts the 'exotic' fauna discovered breeding in the remains of an unlucky intergalactic freighter.

Name: Tentacled Decal
Description:
An exclusive placeable decal, to add a touch of macabre decoration to bases.

This decal depicts a many-armed sentience, found drifting in the dark places of the universe.

Name: Appalling Banner
Description:
Demonstrate your interest in the macabre and the horrific with this exclusive <STELLAR>Personal Flair<>.

Apply this banner to your profile at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Tentacled Banner
Description:
Express your curiosity about abyssal alien lifeforms with this exclusive <STELLAR>Personal Flair<>.

Apply this banner to your profile at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Detoxified Slime
Description:
Gelatinous and slowly pulsing, this puddle of living slime smells sweeter than would be imagined.

Though there is no evidence to suggest it would be unsafe to do so, avoid treading on the slime where possible.

Name: Orange Pustule
Description:
The flesh of this sinister squash is always warm, and slightly luminous. Despite these strange qualities, it is quite edible, and releases a comforting aroma wherever it grows.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Igneous Crystal
Description:
A quiet roar sounds from within this natural crystal formation, lava and gas dancing in a perpetual cycle of heating and solidifying. Mesmerising to the eye, but despite the ultrahot core, only slightly warm to the touch.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Igneous Drop
Description:
This hybrid of egg and rock is known to form around the larvae of certain species, keeping the vulnerable creature warm and protected as it develops over the course of several decades. Membranous splits in the rock's surface expose the ever-shifting molten heart.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

Name: Archaic Habitation Heater
Description:
Although primitive in design, this habitation heater is nonetheless a popular home furnishing. Its hypnotic flames and gentle crackling lend a comforting ambience to any room.

Provides interior decoration opportunities for bases.

Name: Beachhead Expedition Banner
Description:
Equip this exclusive <STELLAR>Personal Flair<> in commemoration of the 'Beachhead' <STELLAR>Expedition<>, and your success in tracking the <SPECIAL>renegade historical echo<>.

Apply this banner to your profile at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Beachhead Expedition Decal
Description:
An exclusive placeable decal, to add flair and decoration to bases.

This decal commemorates the collective effort of the Travellers in mapping the <SPECIAL>Histiographical Flux<> and tracking the renegade echo during the <STELLAR>Beachhead<> Expedition.

Name: Saucer Fungus
Description: This fungal growth, identifiable by its wide, smooth cap and luminescent pores, is native to a variety of cave biomes. Saucer Fungi enjoy a symbiotic relationship with many species of burrowing creatures.

Name: Cave Creeper
Description: A hardy variety of lampenflora. This creeping vine occurs naturally in damp, subterranean environments, but will thrive as a free-standing shrub in any biome type.

Name: Troglotulip
Description: This attractive glowing flower is remarkable for its scent, reminiscent of freshly tilled soil. Due to the plant's mineral-rich diet, the stamens often contain traces of cobalt.

Name: Veined Flat Caps
Description: Clusters of these large mushrooms can be found growing in underground caves. The surface 'veins' form part of an unusual gill structure, releasing spores from both above and below the fungus's cap.

Name: Fingery Deposit
Description: This stalagmite was formed by the dripping of cobalt-rich moisture over several millennia. It is eternally cold to the touch, as though the rock recalls the temperature of its home cave.

Name: Antimatter Observation Orb
Description: This spiked chamber contains a globule of antimatter, creating an unusual display piece for discerning base builders.

Name: Synthesis Core
Description:
A replica of the mysterious orb utilised by Polo's Quicksilver Synthesis Companion.

The physical properties of the orb are forever shifting in strangely rhythmic patterns: temperature, radioactivity and density all fluctuating to an unheard song.

Name: Bubble Vat
Description: A miniaturised replica of the bubbling 'liquid' vat which forms part of the Space Anomaly's anatomy. This mesmerising ornament brings an echo of Polo and Nada's anomalous home to planetary bases.

Name: Bubble Duct
Description:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'.

Intelligently welds into <SPECIAL>different shapes<> to create mesmerising displays in your base.

Name: L-Shaped Bubble Duct
Description:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'. This L-shaped configuration allows for curves in duct connections.

Weld together with different duct shapes to create mesmerising displays in your base.

Name: T-Shaped Bubble Duct
Description:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'. This T-shaped configuration allows for creating branches in duct connections.

Weld together with different duct shapes to create mesmerising displays in your base.

Name: X-Shaped Bubble Duct
Description:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'. This X-shaped configuration allows for connecting four ducts in a cruciform arrangement.

Weld together with different duct shapes to create mesmerising displays in your base.

Name: Settlement Chart
Description: A map showing the location of a nearby planetary settlement, acquired from the Space Station Cartographer<>. Select the map and use Plot Route (FE_ALT1<>) to pin the location in your Exosuit display.
ConsumableRewardTexts: Convert data to Exosuit navigation marker

Name: Alternative Landing Pad
Description: A stable, reinforced landing pad for starships.

Name: Canvas Awning
Description: Draped canvas awning. Can be affixed to structures to provide shade and embellishment.

Name: Twin Flag Awning
Description: Draped canvas awning, fashioned into two discrete flags. Can be affixed to structures to provide shade and embellishment.

Name: Quad Flag Awning
Description: Draped canvas awning, fashioned into four discrete flags. Can be affixed to structures to provide shade and embellishment.

Name: Stone Support Pillar
Description: Stone columns for providing additional support to structural walls.

Name: Water Tower
Description: A large, sturdy reservoir for storing and purifying water and other liquids.

Name: Dish Receptor Antenna
Description: A versatile antenna, fitted with a dish to collect and focus a range of complex interstellar signals.

Name: Tall Antenna
Description: An extra-long antenna, optimised for receiving simple communication signals from interstellar distances.

Name: Dual-Pronged Antenna
Description: An dual-pronged antenna, optimised for receiving complex communication signals from interplanetary distances.

Name: Hanging Flag 1
Description: An ornamental flag suspended from a horizontal pole, for base decoration.

Name: Hanging Flag 2
Description: An ornamental flag suspended from a horizontal pole, for base decoration.

Name: Kite-Patterned Rug
Description: An opulent floor covering with a diamond pattern. Woven from a blend of iridescent sandworm silk and dirt-wicking nano-fibres, this ornate rug is both beautiful and durable.

Name: Kiln-Fired Pot
Description: A gold-rimmed pot for storing anything from potpourri to GekNip to proto-sausage pie. A ceramic blend of ferrite and clay, this ornament lends a rustic touch to base decor.

Name: Upholstered Chair
Description: An elegant moulded chair, upholstered in the softest poly-suede.

Name: Golden Table
Description: This elegant hexagonal table features an inbuilt thermal grille, for maintaining the temperature of cooked products, or for warming or cooling aching fingers.

Name: Wall Light
Description: A low-energy consumption light, with an extended lifespan and fully recyclable components.

Name: Golden Half Counter
Description:
This beautiful golden half counter is coated in a thin layer of living glass, ensuring thermal stability and a scratch-free finish. An illuminated base assists visibility in all lighting conditions.

Place alongside <TECHNOLOGY>Golden Counter<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Golden Counter Corner<> modules to create bespoke counter layouts.

Name: Golden Counter
Description:
This beautiful golden counter is coated in a thin layer of living glass, ensuring thermal stability and a scratch-free finish. An illuminated base assists visibility in all lighting conditions.

Place alongside <TECHNOLOGY>Golden Counter Corner<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Golden Half Counter<> modules to create bespoke counter layouts.

Name: Golden Counter Corner
Description:
This beautiful golden counter corner is coated in a thin layer of living glass, ensuring thermal stability and a scratch-free finish. An illuminated base assists visibility in all lighting conditions.

Place alongside <TECHNOLOGY>Golden Counter<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Golden Half Counter<> modules to create bespoke counter layouts.

Name: Vintage Teapot
Description:
A rustic-styled vessel for brewing and serving hot beverages, crafted in the traditional style of the Gek First Spawn.
This decorative tableware lends a touch of comfort and style to bases.

Name: Table Lamp
Description: A softly-glowing table lamp with self-powered light tubes. Adjustable for focused nighttime reading or ambient lighting.

Name: Vintage Tumbler
Description:
A rustic-styled drinking vessel: forged from a tough copper alloy, blackened with regis grease and laser-sealed.
This decorative tableware lends a touch of comfort and style to bases.

Name: Vintage Dish
Description:
A rustic-styled eating vessel: forged from a tough copper alloy, blackened with regis grease and laser-sealed.
This decorative tableware lends a touch of comfort and style to bases.

Name: Small Box
Description: A carbon fibre reinforced container, sealed for storing perishables.

Name: Oil Burner
Description: A decorative oil burner, self-heated by a concealed reactive core. Transforms any structure into an olfactory delight, filling the air with fragrant bouquets.

Name: Vintage Cooking Pan
Description:
A shallow, double-handled pan for preparing food. Advanced fluoropolymer technology creates a non-stick, self-cleaning surface.
This decorative cookware lends a touch of comfort and style to bases.

Name: Ornate Stool
Description: A stylish three-legged stool, reinforced to support ten times the weight of an average adult Vy'keen. The polyurethane-nanite seat morphs to accommodate the occupant's body shape, making this simple stool surprisingly comfortable.

Name: Reinforced Capsule
Description: A small lead-lined capsule suitable for storing hazardous and radioactive materials.

Name: Vintage Tap
Description: A vintage-styled tap, fitted with laser-enhanced filtration technology. Suitable for dispensing all varieties of liquid, from potable beverages to corrosive acids. Not recommended for use with living slime.

Name: Weathered Hanging
Description: A heavyweight canvas wall decoration. Suspended from Vy'keen Artillery-grade rope, this base adornment is engineered to endure all weather conditions.

Name: Mini Weathered Hangings
Description: A set of four mini canvas wall decorations. Suspended from Vy'keen Artillery-grade rope, this base adornment is engineered to endure all weather conditions.

Name: Weathered Hanging Triptych
Description: A set of three mini canvas wall decorations. Suspended from Vy'keen Artillery-grade rope, this base adornment is engineered to endure all weather conditions.

Name: Stone Trough
Description: A decorative stone trough.

Name: Illuminated Sign
Description: An attention-grabbing welcome sign, illuminated by an array of gas-discharge tubes. Suitable for hanging in commercial premises, or in bases as an eccentric home decoration.

Name: Stepladder
Description: A self-supporting ladder, foldable for convenient transportation.

Name: Scaffolding
Description: Temporary scaffolding, used to access the upper portions of buildings during construction.

Name: Large Scaffolding
Description: Double-width temporary scaffolding, used to access the upper portions of buildings during construction.

Name: Pail
Description: A small pail for disposing of scrap materials.

Name: Tall Bucket
Description: A tall bucket for disposing of scrap materials.

Name: Wooden Pallet
Description: Stackable, robust wooden pallet. Conforms to Universal Construction Standards 3.6a, ensuring compatibility with forklifts developed by all participating alien races.

Name: Brick Pile
Description: A pile of bricks and steel beams, unwrapped and ready for construction.

Name: Cement Bag
Description: A bag of geopolymer cement for mixing into environmentally-friendly, self-healing concrete.

Name: Barricade
Description: Temporary barricade, used cordon off dangerous construction zones.

Name: H-Beam Stack
Description: Stacked steel beams, ideal for constructing support trusses in large structures.

Name: Cement Mixer
Description: Lightweight machinery for mixing cement into concrete.

Name: Shovel
Description: A manual digging implement, still used by some lifeforms for agricultural or construction labour.

Name: Covered Brick Pile
Description: A pile of bricks and steel beams, wrapped and ready for transportation.

Name: Large Tyre
Description: A heavy-duty tyre with all-terrain tread. Fitted with an auto-stabilisation gyroscope and emergency re-inflation pump.

Name: Composter
Description: A living composting system inhabited by a colony of Lumbricus worms. The self-regulating ecosystem processes organic waste and releases nutrients into the local soil.

Name: Small Furnace
Description: An metallurgic furnace with an ultra-fast rise time, capable of melting anything from tin to tungsten within minutes.

Name: Wheelbarrow
Description: A small wheelbarrow for transporting heavy items. Fitted with a microprocessor, it can be pushed manually, or programmed to autonomously execute simple routines.

Name: Excavation Claw
Description: An industrial excavator bucket with self-sharpening chisel teeth, for displacing large quantities of terrain without the use of Multi-Tool technology.

Name: Wash Trough
Description: A sturdy trough with drainage, for washing equipment or watering livestock.

Name: Ventilated Crate
Description: A small vented crate, ideal for ripening or cooling agricultural produce.

Name: Insulated Flask
Description: A sealed vacuum flask ideal for storing launch fuel, liquid nitrogen, or hot beverages.

Name: Sealed Barrel
Description: An industrial sealed barrel, for safe containment of all manner of hazardous material.

Name: Spark Plug
Description: A spare fuel ignition device, compatible with galactic standard industrial machinery and certain models of starship.

Name: Drawn Cart
Description: An unpowered vehicle, with only primitive load-stabilising technology.

Name: Cart Wheel
Description: A spare cart wheel.

Name: Scissor Lift
Description: This electric propulsion scissor lift provides a safe, self-levelling alternative to traditional scaffolding on construction sites.

Name: Industrial Pump
Description: A centrifugal pump for moving liquid, fitted with sensors to detect and auto-evacuate blockages.

Name: Small Generator
Description: A portable thermoelectric generator.

Name: Large Moulded Crate
Description: A mass-produced, lightweight crate.

Name: Moulded Crate
Description: A mass-produced, lightweight crate.

Name: Gas Canister
Description: A gas-filled cylindrical pressure vessel.

Name: Panelled Timber Divider
Description: A large timber barricade, for fencing off or dividing up spaces.
